    <description>Plants annual or perennial, monoecious to subdioecious or less commonly dioecious.
        Leaves usually with or, uncommonly, without Kranz anatomy. Staminate flowers with calyx
        lobes crested or not. Pistillate flowers lacking or rarely with a perianth (in A. covillei,
        A. pleiantha, and A. suckleyi), enclosed by a pair of bracteoles. Bracteoles cuneate to
        ovate or obovate united at least to middle, faces with tubercles or crests or smooth. Seeds
        erect; radicle typically superior (except in A. pleiantha), erect, tip adjacent to
        styles.</description>
